Privacy Policy – Instinct VR

Last updated: 29 January 2026

1. Introduction

Welcome to Instinct VR. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting it. This Privacy Policy explains how data is handled when you use our application.

2. Data We Collect
Meta Horizon Platform Data

Instinct VR uses Meta Horizon platform services to enable core social features. Through these services, the app may access:

Meta user profile display name

Meta user profile image

Leaderboard and achievement data

This data is provided directly by Meta and is used only within the app.

Personal Information

We do not collect or request personal information from users. If you contact us for support, we may receive the information you choose to provide in your message (such as your email address).

3. How We Use Data

We use Meta Horizon platform data solely to:

Display the user’s profile name and image in the in-game user interface

Display names in Meta-managed leaderboards

Unlock Meta-managed achievements

Support communications are used only to respond to user inquiries.

4. Data Storage and Sharing

Instinct VR does not store, sell, rent, or share personal data.

All profile, leaderboard, and achievement data is handled and stored by Meta through its platform services. We do not operate our own servers or databases for user data.

5. Data Security

Because Instinct VR does not store personal data, no personal data is retained on our systems. Meta Horizon platform services manage the security of any platform-provided data.

6. User Rights and Data Deletion

Instinct VR does not retain personal data. Requests regarding Meta profile data, leaderboards, or achievements should be managed through Meta’s account and privacy controls.

If you contact us directly for support and wish to delete related correspondence, you may request deletion via the contact details below.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any updates will be posted with a revised effective date.

8. Contact Us

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact: support@xaltlabs.in
